<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Briton" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Briton</orth> (O. Edd. <emph>Britain</emph>), native of Britain: <bibl n="shak. cym 1.4.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 4, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.67" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 6, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.5.20" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.369" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 369</bibl> etc. Adjectively: <cit><quote>the B. reveller,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.61" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 6, 61</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a B. peasant,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 24</bibl></cit>.
